1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,267
Today, let's start from the beginning.

2
00:00:04,267 --> 00:00:07,112
Even if *interest rates* fall,

3
00:00:07,112 --> 00:00:12,802
this is why home prices don't rise right away.

4
00:00:12,802 --> 00:00:17,354
In the past, the formula was simple.

5
00:00:17,354 --> 00:00:19,345
When rates went down,

6
00:00:19,345 --> 00:00:22,474
borrowing became less burdensome.

7
00:00:22,474 --> 00:00:25,603
Then more money flowed into the market,

8
00:00:25,603 --> 00:00:28,732
and buyers stepped in.

9
00:00:28,732 --> 00:00:31,008
So home prices,

10
00:00:31,008 --> 00:00:34,137
responded almost immediately.

11
00:00:34,137 --> 00:00:37,835
But that's not the case now.

12
00:00:37,835 --> 00:00:39,542
This formula,

13
00:00:39,542 --> 00:00:45,232
doesn't work *automatically* like it used to.

14
00:00:45,232 --> 00:00:49,215
Even Seoul's apartment market,

15
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:52,913
doesn't move right away.

16
00:00:52,913 --> 00:00:54,904
Why is that?

17
00:00:54,904 --> 00:00:57,180
Because real estate now,

18
00:00:57,180 --> 00:01:03,439
doesn't move on interest rates alone anymore.

19
00:01:03,439 --> 00:01:05,430
In today's market,

20
00:01:05,430 --> 00:01:10,551
you have to look at people's *sentiment*.

21
00:01:10,551 --> 00:01:13,396
You also have to look at income,

22
00:01:13,396 --> 00:01:17,379
and the economic outlook too.

23
00:01:17,379 --> 00:01:19,939
If the future feels uncertain,

24
00:01:19,939 --> 00:01:25,914
even a small rate cut won't get people moving.

25
00:01:25,914 --> 00:01:30,181
The backdrop makes it even clearer.

26
00:01:30,181 --> 00:01:31,603
In the past,

27
00:01:31,603 --> 00:01:36,439
as soon as loans became easier to get, people bought.

28
00:01:36,439 --> 00:01:38,999
Now it's different.

29
00:01:38,999 --> 00:01:41,559
Across the Korean economy,

30
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:44,404
uncertainty is high.

31
00:01:44,404 --> 00:01:48,102
There are concerns about slower growth,

32
00:01:48,102 --> 00:01:51,800
and household debt is still a heavy burden.

33
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:55,214
Real income feels stuck.

34
00:01:55,214 --> 00:01:57,774
In this kind of environment,

35
00:01:57,774 --> 00:02:01,188
even if rates come down a little,

36
00:02:01,188 --> 00:02:03,748
it's hard to say,

37
00:02:03,748 --> 00:02:08,015
now is the time to buy a home.

38
00:02:08,015 --> 00:02:10,006
The key, in the end,

39
00:02:10,006 --> 00:02:12,851
is *buyer sentiment*.

40
00:02:12,851 --> 00:02:18,541
Home prices don't rise just because of the numbers.

41
00:02:18,541 --> 00:02:22,808
People have to feel like,

42
00:02:22,808 --> 00:02:26,791
now is a good time to buy.

43
00:02:26,791 --> 00:02:30,774
Even in Seoul's apartment market right now,

44
00:02:30,774 --> 00:02:35,041
some high-demand areas are holding up.

45
00:02:35,041 --> 00:02:38,170
But overall,

46
00:02:38,170 --> 00:02:40,730
conviction is weak.

47
00:02:40,730 --> 00:02:43,575
Will prices go higher from here?

48
00:02:43,575 --> 00:02:46,704
People just aren't sure.

49
00:02:46,704 --> 00:02:50,118
Will the economy hold up?

50
00:02:50,118 --> 00:02:53,816
They're not confident about that either.

51
00:02:53,816 --> 00:02:56,661
Will my income hold up?

52
00:02:56,661 --> 00:02:59,506
That's uncertain too.

53
00:02:59,506 --> 00:03:02,351
Without that confidence,

54
00:03:02,351 --> 00:03:07,187
transactions don't come back easily.

55
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:12,308
There's an important point here.

56
00:03:12,308 --> 00:03:17,714
A *rate cut* is not always,

57
00:03:17,714 --> 00:03:20,274
a positive signal.

58
00:03:20,274 --> 00:03:23,119
Of course, rate cuts,

59
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:27,671
can be positive for the market.

60
00:03:27,671 --> 00:03:30,516
But on their own,

61
00:03:30,516 --> 00:03:33,930
they are not a magic signal.

62
00:03:33,930 --> 00:03:37,059
In fact, if a rate cut,

63
00:03:37,059 --> 00:03:42,465
is meant to prevent an economic downturn,

64
00:03:42,465 --> 00:03:47,017
people read it differently.

65
00:03:47,017 --> 00:03:47,586
Oh,

66
00:03:47,586 --> 00:03:51,284
maybe things aren't looking good.

67
00:03:51,284 --> 00:03:55,267
That's how they may take it.

68
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:59,819
Then even if lending conditions improve,

69
00:03:59,819 --> 00:04:04,655
they don't immediately start buying aggressively.

70
00:04:04,655 --> 00:04:09,776
Instead, they try to protect their *cash*.

71
00:04:09,776 --> 00:04:12,905
Right now, this kind of sentiment,

72
00:04:12,905 --> 00:04:17,172
has an even bigger impact on the market.

73
00:04:17,172 --> 00:04:20,586
That's why even if rates fall,

74
00:04:20,586 --> 00:04:24,284
you shouldn't assume,

75
00:04:24,284 --> 00:04:27,982
that home prices will automatically go up.

76
00:04:27,982 --> 00:04:32,818
There's one more thing to watch.

77
00:04:32,818 --> 00:04:35,094
Seoul apartments, too,

78
00:04:35,094 --> 00:04:39,361
do not all move together.

79
00:04:39,361 --> 00:04:42,775
Even under the same rate environment,

80
00:04:42,775 --> 00:04:47,042
prime areas respond differently.

81
00:04:47,042 --> 00:04:49,033
Places with strong locations,

82
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:52,162
and solid demand,

83
00:04:52,162 --> 00:04:57,568
can hold up or even rebound somewhat.

84
00:04:57,568 --> 00:05:01,266
Outlying areas are different.

85
00:05:01,266 --> 00:05:04,395
In areas with weaker demand,

86
00:05:04,395 --> 00:05:07,809
the response is much slower.

87
00:05:07,809 --> 00:05:11,507
Why does this gap happen?

88
00:05:11,507 --> 00:05:13,498
Because today's market,

89
00:05:13,498 --> 00:05:16,343
looks at more than just *rates alone*.

90
00:05:16,343 --> 00:05:21,464
It looks at supply conditions,

91
00:05:21,464 --> 00:05:23,740
whether local demand is there,

92
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:26,869
whether incomes can support prices,

93
00:05:26,869 --> 00:05:30,567
and whether sentiment is recovering.

94
00:05:30,567 --> 00:05:33,412
These factors have become more important.

95
00:05:33,412 --> 00:05:38,248
In the end, the simple formula from the past,

96
00:05:38,248 --> 00:05:42,515
has lost much of its power.

97
00:05:42,515 --> 00:05:45,360
Now you have to look at the market more broadly.

98
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:50,766
So then,

99
00:05:50,766 --> 00:05:52,757
what should we be watching now?

100
00:05:52,757 --> 00:05:55,886
First,

101
00:05:55,886 --> 00:05:56,739
whether buyer sentiment is recovering.

102
00:05:56,739 --> 00:06:01,006
You need to see whether people are done waiting,

103
00:06:01,006 --> 00:06:04,704
and are actually starting to move.

104
00:06:04,704 --> 00:06:09,256
Second,

105
00:06:09,256 --> 00:06:10,109
whether *transaction volume* is picking up.

106
00:06:10,109 --> 00:06:14,092
Before prices recover, transactions have to come back first,

107
00:06:14,092 --> 00:06:18,928
for the momentum to continue.

108
00:06:18,928 --> 00:06:21,773
Third,

109
00:06:21,773 --> 00:06:22,626
whether demand is recovering by area.

110
00:06:22,626 --> 00:06:26,324
Even within Seoul,

111
00:06:26,324 --> 00:06:28,600
you need to see which areas move first,

112
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:32,298
and watch the gap between them.

113
00:06:32,298 --> 00:06:35,996
Only when these three come together,

114
00:06:35,996 --> 00:06:39,410
does a rate cut translate into actual price gains.

115
00:06:39,410 --> 00:06:45,385
To sum it up.

116
00:06:45,385 --> 00:06:47,945
Today's market,

117
00:06:47,945 --> 00:06:49,936
can't be explained by a rate cut alone.

118
00:06:49,936 --> 00:06:55,911
What matters more,

119
00:06:55,911 --> 00:06:57,618
is what kind of signal people take from it afterward.

120
00:06:57,618 --> 00:07:02,170
If they feel anxious,

121
00:07:02,170 --> 00:07:05,299
rates can fall and transactions still won't pick up.

122
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:07,575
If they feel confident,

123
00:07:07,575 --> 00:07:12,981
that's when the market starts moving.

124
00:07:12,981 --> 00:07:15,257
So going forward,

125
00:07:15,257 --> 00:07:19,524
don't just watch rates.

126
00:07:19,524 --> 00:07:22,084
You also need to watch *sentiment*, *transaction volume*, and *local demand*,

127
00:07:22,084 --> 00:07:25,213
together.

128
00:07:25,213 --> 00:07:31,472
The direction of home prices,

129
00:07:31,472 --> 00:07:34,601
depends more heavily on these three factors.

130
00:07:34,601 --> 00:07:36,592
What is your area like right now?

131
00:07:36,592 --> 00:07:41,998
Are you seeing the impact of rates right away?

132
00:07:41,998 --> 00:07:46,550
Or is it still quiet?

133
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:50,817
Leave a comment,

134
00:07:50,817 --> 00:07:54,515
and let's take a look together.

135
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:57,360


136
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,920

